{
  "texts": [
    "The Microsoft News Dataset (MIND) serves as a comprehensive benchmark for evaluating news recommendation systems (Wu et al. 2020).",
    "It contains millions of news articles and user click histories collected from the Microsoft News platform.",
    "The dataset is bifurcated into two primary subsets MIND-small and MIND-large.",
    "As delineated in Table 1, MIND-small contains over 65K news articles and approximately 230K user impressions, while MIND-large expands this to over 161K articles and nearly 16 million impressions.",
    "The dataset provides rich textual content including titles, abstracts, categories, and subcategories."
  ]
}